  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, the monsoon is here — I'm feeling hopeful today. How was your team meeting about the new app feature?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was okay. We discussed the payment gateway part. I think we need more time, but the deadline is near. By the way, did you see the latest Salman Khan movie? It’s called \"Dabangg 3\", I think."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — deadlines are tricky. 'Dabangg 3' sounds familiar. I'll watch it soon. Did you enjoy the first one?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, the first one was good. Salman Khan's movies usually have good action and some nice songs. I remember watching it back in 2010, I think. But I prefer the newer ones because the technology looks better now. By the way, do you like Bollywood movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Bollywood has its classics! Salman Khan’s style is fun — action and songs work well together. I do like Bollywood movies. What’s your favourite actor or actress?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Amitabh Bachchan is my favorite actor. His voice and acting are iconic. I also like Deepika Padukone. She has some good recent movies. Have you seen \"Chennai Express\"? It's a fun movie with lots of comedy and music."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Amitabh Bachchan is a legend — his voice is unforgettable. Deepika Padukone has some great films too. *Chennai Express* was a fun watch! Do you often go to the cinema for new movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not really. I prefer watching movies at home. Maybe once in a while if a friend suggests it. Theatres are nice for big action films, but I find it more comfortable at home. What about you? Do you go to the cinema?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I agree — home is best for comfort, but theatres are great for big action films. I watch mostly at home. What’s your go-to snack while watching movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually have popcorn or some chips. Sometimes I also have tea or cold drinks. For Bollywood movies, I like to have some chaat — maybe aloo tikki or something spicy. What about you? Do you have a favorite snack?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I love a good chaat — spicy and tangy hits the spot! Tea pairs well with it. I’m a tea person too. What chaat do you like best?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like golgappa the most — the one with puffed puris and tamarind water. It’s crispy and spicy. Sometimes I also eat bhel puri. Do you like those?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Golgappa is a perfect mix of crispy and tangy — I agree! Bhel puri is another monsoon favourite. Do you make them at home or buy from a street vendor?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I sometimes buy them from a local vendor, but during monsoon, my mom makes bhel puri at home. It’s tasty! I prefer homemade if I can get it. Have you tried making chaat at home?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Homemade chaat is always the best — so much flavour! I haven’t made it myself, but I’d love to learn. Do you have a recipe you like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not really, but I can suggest one. My mom's bhel puri recipe is simple — puffed rice, sev, tamarind chutney, and green chutney. Sometimes she adds peas or potatoes. It's quick and tasty. Maybe I can ask her for the exact steps and share it with you!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds delicious — simple but full of taste! I’d love to try it. Ask your mom if she has any special tips for the chutney. Would you make it with spicy or sweet chutney?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We usually use spicy tamarind chutney, but sometimes she makes a sweet one with jaggery. The spicy one goes best with bhel puri, I think. Let me check with her and tell you more. Oh, and bhel puri is best when it’s fresh — the puffed rice stays crispy longer if you make it just before eating. Gotta go now, but I’ll talk to her and share the recipe!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — spicy chutney is the classic choice. Fresh bhel puri is the best, no doubt! Talk to you soon about the recipe. Have a great day!"
    }
  ],
